==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cylindroid
<hw>Cyl"in*droid</hw> <pr>(s?l"?n-droid)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ky`lindros</grk> cylinder + <ets>-oid</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>cylindro⟦ium⟧de</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A solid body
resembling a right cylinder, but having the bases or ends
elliptical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A certain surface of the third
degree, described by a moving straight line; -- used to illustrate the
motions of a rigid body and also the forces acting on the
body.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cylindrometric</ent>⟦br⟧
